description._content: Collection: NASA Great Images in Nasa Collection Title: Apollo 11 Launch Spectators Full Description: These three were among the thousands of persons who camped on beaches and roads adjacent to the Kennedy Space Center to watch the Apollo launch. An estimated one million persons visited the Spaceport area to see the historic flight, this nation's first attempt to land Americans on the lunar surface.
